ht, he asked not for an arrow but for a gaze. Politics smelled like hot pitch on a wet wind, and the quay it built in the mind was narrow: too slick to stand still, too crowded to run, and edged with water that remembered every name thrown into it.\",\n      \"objectives\": [\n        \"Inspect the fuel and wicks of the vote-lamps for moon-resin adulteration before the floor bell rings.\",\n        \"Shadow the mirrored listening passage and note any Rookery brokers coordinating the timing of interruptions.\",\n        \"Decide how to handle a discovered forged moon-flame: expose it publicly to Ista Brine, or swap it silently to prevent a scandal without implicating allies.\",\n        \"Protect Talo Ren during the vote from a staged stumble designed to spill saffron dye onto tally cords.\",\n        \"Deliver your findings to either the Speaker or the Archivists for record.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\n          \"speaker\": \"Talo Ren\",\n          \"lines\": \"You make a habit of plucking the city out of its own teeth, Neris, and I have not forgotten the line you cast when the river tried to turn Parliament into driftwood. I would like to believe we are steadied by principles, but I have seen how easily a colored flame can teach a lie to pass for order. Tonight I ask for your eye more than your string, because a good eye is a lamp that no hand can cup, and the count must be lit by truth or it burns us all. If a flame lies in this hall, I must know before I raise the tray and kindle the tally, or I become another man who says flood to hide theft, another Speaker who mistakes spectacle for safety. Help me keep this vote upright, even if it tilts the world against me tomorrow, because I would rather be hated in daylight than praised by a darkness I helped pour.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"speaker\": \"Clerk-Marshal Ista Brine\",\n          \"lines\": \"If you find a counterfeit flame, you bring it to my desk with the wick still warm, and 